Unwise.  Pc3 nets white that black bishop.  Or if black moves the bishop, white trades a rook for the black queen, undoing a good part of black's material advantage.  Then again, Qg5+ or Qe7 trades bishop for bishop.  So nabbing the pawn isn't that bad after all.  Carry on...

Ok, Bd5 is a classic pin.

I still like Bd5--it keeps the white rook from moving, and should ultimately make for a quicker game.  Failing that, Rd2 might be better than Rd1.  This would confine white's rook to the b column (or QxPb2#).
